wikipedia_page.main: Stephen Clissold (17 February 1825 – 26 May 1898) was an English cricketer. He played eight first-class matches for Cambridge University Cricket Club between 1844 and 1848.

response: Born in or about 1797, the fifth son of Stephen Clissold (1764–1834) of Stonehouse, near Stroud, Gloucestershire, he had Stephen Clissold the writer as an elder brother. He matriculated at Exeter College, Oxford on 6 December 1814, the same day as his elder brother Henry. He took the ordinary B.A. degree on 19 November 1818, proceeding M.A. on 13 June 1821.
